{"version": 2, "width": 80, "height": 24, "timestamp": 1782485863, "idle_time_limit": 2.0, "env": {"SHELL": "/usr/bin/zsh", "TERM": "xterm-256color"}}
[0.005069, "o", "\u001b[36m# An AI agent connects to MCP servers. Each one hands it tools.\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36m# Which of those tools are a compliance problem, and how do you contain them?\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.507565, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1m# Step 1: discover what the agent can actually do\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[90m$ agentic-compliance-scan --discover mcp-config.json > my-agent.json\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[7.488732, "o", "\u001b[32m"]
[7.491404, "o", "# filesystem: discovered 14 tool(s)\r\n"]
[7.491794, "o", "\u001b[0m\u001b[90m# tools listed and effects classified, no hand-listing.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[9.995084, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1m# Step 2: scan against the law, for Germany\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[90m$ agentic-compliance-scan --inventory my-agent.json --jurisdiction DE\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[10.261683, "o", "11 gap(s) found (high: 6, medium: 5).\r\n## National law (DE)\r\n### [high] Agent acts on an in-scope system with no risk analysis and information system security policies declared\r\n- Reference: NIS2 § 30 Abs. 2 Nr. 1 BSIG, DE BSIG (NIS2UmsuCG 2025)\r\n"]
[13.26374, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1m# Step 3: recommend the policy to lock down the dangerous tools, on any gateway\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[90m$ agentic-compliance-scan --policy my-agent.json\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[13.51476, "o", "## wm-mcp-server:setup_user_management (require human approval)\r\n- Match: tools/call where params.name == \"setup_user_management\"\r\n## wm-mcp-server:setup_oauth (require human approval)\r\n- Match: tools/call where params.name == \"setup_oauth\"\r\n"]
[13.515237, "o", "\u001b[90m# add --gateway webmethods (or envoy) for a ready-to-paste snippet\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[16.517687, "o", "\r\n\u001b[33m\u001b[1m# The full loop:\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[33m# discover a real MCP server, cite the gaps in your own national law,\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[33m# and recommend the policy to close them, on any gateway. In seconds.\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[90m# github.com/cpoder/agentic-compliance-scan\u001b[0m\r\n"]
